This paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for video analysis and action recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of residual learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the design of a new spatiotemporal convolutional block, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also discusses the empirical study and comparison of different convolutional methods, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of CNNs for achieving state-of-the-art results, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
